## The Ralph Loop

At the heart of powerglide is the **Ralph Loop** — a state machine that drives every agent session:

```zig
pub const LoopState = enum {
    idle,
    thinking,
    acting,
    observing,
    finished,
    failed,
};
```

### State Transitions

```=html
<svg viewBox="0 0 800 200" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
  <defs>
    <linearGradient id="pg-gradient" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="100%">
      <stop offset="0%" style="stop-color:#F7A41D;stop-opacity:1"/>
      <stop offset="100%" style="stop-color:#d97706;stop-opacity:1"/>
    </linearGradient>
    <linearGradient id="cyan-gradient" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="100%">
      <stop offset="0%" style="stop-color:#06b6d4;stop-opacity:1"/>
      <stop offset="100%" style="stop-color:#0891b2;stop-opacity:1"/>
    </linearGradient>
    <linearGradient id="purple-gradient" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="100%">
      <stop offset="0%" style="stop-color:#7c3aed;stop-opacity:1"/>
      <stop offset="100%" style="stop-color:#6d28d9;stop-opacity:1"/>
    </linearGradient>
    <filter id="neon-glow" x="-50%" y="-50%" width="200%" height="200%">
      <feGaussianBlur in="SourceGraphic" stdDeviation="2" result="blur1"/>
      <feGaussianBlur in="SourceGraphic" stdDeviation="4" result="blur2"/>
      <feMerge>
        <feMergeNode in="blur2"/>
        <feMergeNode in="blur1"/>
        <feMergeNode in="SourceGraphic"/>
      </feMerge>
    </filter>
    <filter id="soft-glow" x="-50%" y="-50%" width="200%" height="200%">
      <feGaussianBlur in="SourceGraphic" stdDeviation="3" result="blur"/>
      <feMerge>
        <feMergeNode in="blur"/>
        <feMergeNode in="SourceGraphic"/>
      </feMerge>
    </filter>
    <marker id="arrowhead" markerWidth="10" markerHeight="7" refX="9" refY="3.5" orient="auto">
      <polygon points="0 0, 10 3.5, 0 7" fill="#F7A41D"/>
    </marker>
  </defs>

  <!-- Background -->
  <rect width="800" height="200" fill="#050505" rx="8"/>

  <!-- Cyber grid pattern -->
  <g stroke="#1a1a25" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.5">
    <line x1="100" y1="0" x2="100" y2="200"/>
    <line x1="200" y1="0" x2="200" y2="200"/>
    <line x1="300" y1="0" x2="300" y2="200"/>
    <line x1="400" y1="0" x2="400" y2="200"/>
    <line x1="500" y1="0" x2="500" y2="200"/>
    <line x1="600" y1="0" x2="600" y2="200"/>
    <line x1="700" y1="0" x2="700" y2="200"/>
    <line x1="0" y1="100" x2="800" y2="100"/>
  </g>

  <!-- State boxes -->
  <!-- IDLE -->
  <rect x="30" y="80" width="100" height="40" fill="none" stroke="url(#pg-gradient)" stroke-width="2" rx="4" filter="url(#soft-glow)"/>
  <text x="80" y="105" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="14" font-weight="bold" font-family="monospace">IDLE</text>

  <!-- LOAD_TASKS -->
  <rect x="170" y="80" width="120" height="40" fill="none" stroke="url(#cyan-gradient)" stroke-width="2" rx="4" filter="url(#soft-glow)"/>
  <text x="230" y="105" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="14" font-weight="bold" font-family="monospace">LOAD_TASKS</text>

  <!-- THINKING -->
  <rect x="330" y="80" width="100" height="40" fill="none" stroke="url(#cyan-gradient)" stroke-width="2" rx="4" filter="url(#soft-glow)"/>
  <text x="380" y="105" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="14" font-weight="bold" font-family="monospace">THINKING</text>

  <!-- ACTING -->
  <rect x="470" y="80" width="100" height="40" fill="none" stroke="url(#cyan-gradient)" stroke-width="2" rx="4" filter="url(#soft-glow)"/>
  <text x="520" y="105" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="14" font-weight="bold" font-family="monospace">ACTING</text>

  <!-- OBSERVING -->
  <rect x="610" y="80" width="110" height="40" fill="none" stroke="url(#cyan-gradient)" stroke-width="2" rx="4" filter="url(#soft-glow)"/>
  <text x="665" y="105" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="14" font-weight="bold" font-family="monospace">OBSERVING</text>

  <!-- VERIFY/COMMIT -->
  <rect x="610" y="150" width="110" height="40" fill="none" stroke="url(#purple-gradient)" stroke-width="2" rx="4" filter="url(#soft-glow)"/>
  <text x="665" y="175" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="12" font-weight="bold" font-family="monospace">VERIFY/COMMIT</text>

  <!-- Arrows -->
  <!-- IDLE -> LOAD_TASKS -->
  <line x1="130" y1="100" x2="165" y2="100" stroke="#F7A41D" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arrowhead)"/>

  <!-- LOAD_TASKS -> THINKING -->
  <line x1="290" y1="100" x2="325" y2="100" stroke="#F7A41D" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arrowhead)"/>

  <!-- THINKING -> ACTING -->
  <line x1="430" y1="100" x2="465" y2="100" stroke="#F7A41D" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arrowhead)"/>

  <!-- ACTING -> OBSERVING -->
  <line x1="570" y1="100" x2="605" y2="100" stroke="#F7A41D" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arrowhead)"/>

  <!-- OBSERVING -> VERIFY/COMMIT -->
  <line x1="665" y1="120" x2="665" y2="145" stroke="#F7A41D" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arrowhead)"/>

  <!-- VERIFY/COMMIT -> LOAD_TASKS (loop back) -->
  <path d="M 610 170 Q 230 170 230 125" fill="none" stroke="#7c3aed" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arrowhead)" stroke-dasharray="5,5"/>

  <!-- Corner accents -->
  <g stroke="#7c3aed" stroke-width="2" fill="none" opacity="0.5">
    <path d="M20 20 L30 20 L30 30"/>
    <path d="M780 20 L770 20 L770 30"/>
    <path d="M20 180 L30 180 L30 170"/>
    <path d="M780 180 L770 180 L770 170"/>
  </g>
</svg>
```

The loop emits `<POWERGLIDE_DONE>` when all tasks are complete.

## Multi-Agent Swarm Architecture

```=html
<svg viewBox="0 0 700 350" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
  <defs>
    <linearGradient id="pg-gradient" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="100%">
      <stop offset="0%" style="stop-color:#F7A41D;stop-opacity:1"/>
      <stop offset="100%" style="stop-color:#d97706;stop-opacity:1"/>
    </linearGradient>
    <linearGradient id="cyan-gradient" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="100%">
      <stop offset="0%" style="stop-color:#06b6d4;stop-opacity:1"/>
      <stop offset="100%" style="stop-color:#0891b2;stop-opacity:1"/>
    </linearGradient>
    <linearGradient id="purple-gradient" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="100%">
      <stop offset="0%" style="stop-color:#7c3aed;stop-opacity:1"/>
      <stop offset="100%" style="stop-color:#6d28d9;stop-opacity:1"/>
    </linearGradient>
    <filter id="neon-glow" x="-50%" y="-50%" width="200%" height="200%">
      <feGaussianBlur in="SourceGraphic" stdDeviation="2" result="blur1"/>
      <feGaussianBlur in="SourceGraphic" stdDeviation="4" result="blur2"/>
      <feMerge>
        <feMergeNode in="blur2"/>
        <feMergeNode in="blur1"/>
        <feMergeNode in="SourceGraphic"/>
      </feMerge>
    </filter>
    <filter id="soft-glow" x="-50%" y="-50%" width="200%" height="200%">
      <feGaussianBlur in="SourceGraphic" stdDeviation="3" result="blur"/>
      <feMerge>
        <feMergeNode in="blur"/>
        <feMergeNode in="SourceGraphic"/>
      </feMerge>
    </filter>
    <marker id="arrowhead" markerWidth="10" markerHeight="7" refX="9" refY="3.5" orient="auto">
      <polygon points="0 0, 10 3.5, 0 7" fill="#F7A41D"/>
    </marker>
  </defs>

  <!-- Background -->
  <rect width="700" height="350" fill="#050505" rx="8"/>

  <!-- Cyber grid pattern -->
  <g stroke="#1a1a25" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.5">
    <line x1="100" y1="0" x2="100" y2="350"/>
    <line x1="200" y1="0" x2="200" y2="350"/>
    <line x1="300" y1="0" x2="300" y2="350"/>
    <line x1="400" y1="0" x2="400" y2="350"/>
    <line x1="500" y1="0" x2="500" y2="350"/>
    <line x1="600" y1="0" x2="600" y2="350"/>
    <line x1="0" y1="100" x2="700" y2="100"/>
    <line x1="0" y1="200" x2="700" y2="200"/>
    <line x1="0" y1="300" x2="700" y2="300"/>
  </g>

  <!-- Orchestrator Section -->
  <rect x="50" y="40" width="600" height="130" fill="none" stroke="url(#purple-gradient)" stroke-width="2" rx="8" filter="url(#soft-glow)"/>
  <text x="350" y="65" text-anchor="middle" fill="#7c3aed" font-size="16" font-weight="bold" font-family="monospace" filter="url(#neon-glow)">Orchestrator (slow, powerful model)</text>

  <!-- Orchestrator items -->
  <g fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="12" font-family="monospace">
    <text x="70" y="95">• assigns tasks via task-queue.json</text>
    <text x="70" y="120">• monitors worker heartbeats</text>
    <text x="70" y="145">• aggregates results</text>
  </g>

  <!-- Workers Section -->
  <rect x="50" y="200" width="600" height="130" fill="none" stroke="url(#cyan-gradient)" stroke-width="2" rx="8" filter="url(#soft-glow)"/>
  <text x="350" y="225" text-anchor="middle" fill="#06b6d4" font-size="16" font-weight="bold" font-family="monospace" filter="url(#neon-glow)">Workers (fast models) × N</text>

  <!-- Workers items -->
  <g fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="12" font-family="monospace">
    <text x="70" y="255">• each has isolated workspace</text>
    <text x="70" y="280">• pulls tasks from queue</text>
    <text x="70" y="305">• writes progress to worker-{id}.json</text>
    <text x="70" y="330">• signals completion via done-{id}.json</text>
  </g>

  <!-- Connection arrow -->
  <path d="M 350 170 L 350 195" stroke="#F7A41D" stroke-width="3" marker-end="url(#arrowhead)" filter="url(#soft-glow)"/>

  <!-- Corner accents -->
  <g stroke="#7c3aed" stroke-width="2" fill="none" opacity="0.5">
    <path d="M20 20 L30 20 L30 30"/>
    <path d="M680 20 L670 20 L670 30"/>
    <path d="M20 330 L30 330 L30 320"/>
    <path d="M680 330 L670 330 L670 320"/>
  </g>
</svg>
```

Inter-agent communication is file-based at `~/.powerglide/teams/{team-id}/messages/`.

## Rogue Agent Prevention

powerglide includes multi-layer rogue agent prevention:

| Mechanism | Default | Description |
|-----------|---------|-------------|
| Step limit | 200 | Kill after N steps regardless |
| Heartbeat | 30s | Worker must write heartbeat; monitor kills if missed |
| Circuit breaker | 3 repeats | Kill if same tool called with same args 3+ times |
| Budget tracking | configurable | Stop if token/cost budget exceeded |
| Explicit done signal | required | Agent must emit `POWERGLIDE_DONE` to terminate cleanly |

## Velocity Control

Velocity controls how fast the ralph loop progresses:

```bash
powerglide run --velocity 2.0  # 2x speed: 500ms between steps
powerglide run --velocity 0.5  # 0.5x speed: 2000ms between steps
```

Agents can self-adjust velocity by writing `VELOCITY=<value>` to their session config file at `~/.config/powerglide/session-<id>.json`. The orchestrator polls this file every N steps.

## Configuration Loading

Configuration is loaded in order of precedence:

1. Command-line arguments (highest priority)
2. Environment variables
3. `~/.config/powerglide/config.json`
4. Built-in defaults (lowest priority)

```zig
const config = Config.load(.{
    .cli_args = args,
    .env = std.process.env,
    .config_file = "~/.config/powerglide/config.json",
});
```

## Tool Interface

All tools implement a common interface:

```zig
pub const Tool = struct {
    name: []const u8,
    description: []const u8,
    parameters: ?[]const u8 = null,
    
    pub fn execute(self: *Tool, args: []const u8) !ToolResult {
        // Implementation
    }
};

pub const ToolResult = struct {
    success: bool,
    output: []const u8,
    err: ?[]const u8 = null,
};
```

